Author: phil26
Content:
Hello,
Problem in testnet (cairo-lang 0.12.0), with cairo v2.0.0 contract :
`Read/Write Contract` do not list functions .
Probably due  to the new format of ABI in v2.0.0.

Author: 0xjon#0981
Content: could you link to the contract?

Author: 0xjon#0981
Content: thanks

Author: 0xjon#0981
Content: do you know where i can find docs on the new abi format?

Author: phil26
Content: There is no doc. I am working with the team of Starknet.js to implement this new format.

Author: phil26
Content:
All functions are now in level 2, under the type `interface`.
Constructor is a new type, in level 1.

Author: phil26
Content: Pay a special attention to a new type : `enum`

Author: phil26
Content: You can use the abi of my example. It includes all the existing types.
